==English==

sometimes written: puzzle hunt

===Etymology===
puzzle + hunt (coined by Bruce Leban in 1998 for the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Puzzle_Hunt| Microsoft Puzzlehunt])

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{{1|A puzzlehunt is a game where teams compete to solve puzzles, the answers to which reveal the location of a hidden treasure or allow the teams to accomplish a final goal. The puzzle answers are frequently combined in a [[metapuzzle]].}}}

